Additional Terms:

1. AI-Generated Content
   a. Content generated through OpenAI's services is subject to OpenAI's terms of
      service and usage guidelines (https://openai.com/policies/terms-of-use).
   b. Illustrations created via Stable Diffusion are subject to the CreativeML
      Open RAIL-M license terms (https://huggingface.co/spaces/CompVis/stable-diffusion-license).
   c. Users retain rights to their personalized story content while granting
      Memorable Platform necessary licenses to process and generate books.

2. Third-Party Acknowledgments
   This software integrates with and relies upon various third-party services:
   - OpenAI API (Commercial License)
   - Stable Diffusion (CreativeML Open RAIL-M)
   - Print Network Services (Commercial Agreements)
   - Various open-source packages under MIT-compatible licenses

3. User Content and Privacy
   a. Users retain ownership of all personal content uploaded to the platform.
   b. The platform is granted limited rights to process, store, and print
      user-provided content solely for book creation purposes.
   c. All user data handling must comply with GDPR, CCPA, and COPPA requirements.

4. Print Rights and Distribution
   a. Physical book printing rights are limited to authorized print network partners.
   b. Digital preview and proof copies are for personal use only.
   c. Commercial redistribution of generated books requires explicit authorization.

5. Geographic Restrictions
   Initial service coverage is limited to North America and Western Europe.
   Additional regions may be covered under separate terms.

6. Modifications and Derivatives
   Any modifications to the core platform must:
   a. Maintain compatibility with all third-party service terms
   b. Preserve all privacy and data protection measures
   c. Comply with AI ethical guidelines and content restrictions
   d. Maintain print quality standards and specifications

7. Ethical AI Usage
   Platform usage must adhere to ethical AI principles including:
   a. Prevention of harmful or discriminatory content generation
   b. Protection of minor's privacy and interests
   c. Transparency in AI-generated content identification
   d. Responsible content filtering and moderation

8. Warranty and Liability
   In addition to MIT License limitations:
   a. No warranties are provided for AI-generated content accuracy
   b. Print quality is subject to partner network capabilities
   c. Service availability depends on third-party API accessibility

